rounds.response:
We’ve got an ace-high paired board (3-3-A♠) and two opponents who each voluntarily paid 20 pre-flop (SB posted 10, BB posted 20 and was effectively raised 10 by the SB’s call). That range is wide—everything from real 3’s, overpairs, and ace-x to random broadways and suited junk.

My holding is Q♦ J♠—no pair, no flush draw, just a gut-shot wheel (needs a T) and two overcards. Equity versus typical defend ranges is low; we’re roughly 25 % against many Ace-x holdings and crushed by any 3, A-x, pocket pair ≥88.

The pot is only 40 chips and we’re out of position against two opponents; continuing would be lighting money on fire. Fold and live to fight hands we can actually leverage.

[Fold]
